description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An outstanding individual is sought to fulfil the role of Training Programme Director – Clinical Endoscopy. Accountable to the Postgraduate Dean. You will play an important part in the direction of training programmes across Health Education England South West. Specific roles and responsibilities will be discussed at interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ideal candidate will be an experienced NHS Consultant with a thorough understanding of Gastroenterology / Clinical Endoscopy training across the region and who will also have strong leadership and communication skills and be able to work effectively as a member of a multi-professional team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post will be available on the basis of a secondment arrangement to HEE SW remunerated on the NHS Consultant Pay Scale – 6 PAs per week. We would welcome applications to job share this post as this could help to provide greater coverage across our geographically wide region. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;All work undertaken is to be incorporated into the Consultant Job Plan.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a HEE SW wide role and the successful candidate(s) will have knowledge of all rotations and trainees. They will be expected to cover for any other TPD CE during periods of absence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;When we are able to return to an office base environment, the primary location for the successful candidate’s location will be Park House, Bristol or Plummer House, Plymouth. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will generally work remotely, using MS Teams, following current NHS guidance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Geoff Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Regional Postgraduate Dean, South West&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: geoff.smith2@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01752 590625&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark Wilson - Workforce Transformation Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mark.Wilson@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
